    <h1>Connecting to GRCC Remote Access</h1> 
    <h3><u>!!! - A notice about shortcuts - !!!</u></h3> 
    <p class="cont"> You may experience problems accessing the remote access website when trying to use a shortcut, bookmark, or favorite. Please ensure that your favorite is linked only to the base URL. Any additions to the path (anything after the .edu/) could change with minor or major updates.<br><br> The following is an example of a valid path:</p> 
    <p class="pindent">https://remote.greenriver.edu</p> 
    <p class="cont">The following is an example of an invalid path:</p> 
    <p class="pindent">https://remote.greeriver.edu/<b>citrix/metaframe/</b></p>
    <br>
    <br> 
    <h3><u>!!! - A notice about personal firewall software - !!!</u></h3> 
    <p class="cont"> Some personal firewall software products may prevent the GRCC Remote Desktop from launching. In some cases, the firewall software blocks this access without notification. If nothing seems to happen after clicking on the GRCC Remote Desktop icon, please check your firewall software configuration. Some products may require you to "allow" the program (wfica32.exe), others may require you to "allow" the remote access server's IP address (134.39.100.43). </p> 
    <br> 
    <h3><u>!!! - Attention Mac Users - !!!</u></h3> 
    <p class="cont"> The process for connecting to Remote Access on a Mac is a little more involved than on a PC. This is because Macs do not get regular root and intermediate certificate updates. Manual updating of the root and intermediate certificates is required on Macs. </p> 
    <p class="pindent"><a href="http://remote.greenriver.edu/Mac-RA-Instructs.pdf">Click here to download a PDF document with instructions on connecting to<br>Remote Access with your Macintosh computer.</a></p> 
    <br> 
    <h3><u>!!! - Attention PC Users - !!!</u></h3> 
    <p class="cont"> Some users may need to follow the processes below when connecting to Remote Access for the first time on a particular computer. </p> 
    <h3><u>Adding the GRCC Remote Access site to Internet Explorer's Trusted Sites:</u></h3> 
    <ul> 
     <li>Open the Internet Explorer web browser.</li> 
     <li>Select <b><i>Tools</i></b>, and then select <b><i>Internet Options</i></b>.</li> 
     <li>Select the tab labeled <b><i>Security</i></b>.</li> 
     <li>Select <b><i>Trusted sites</i></b> and click on the button labeled <b><i>Sites</i></b>.</li> 
     <li>Enter <i><b>https://remote.greenriver.edu</b></i>, click the <i><b>Add</b></i> button, then click <b><i>Close</i></b>.</li> 
     <li>Click <b><i>OK</i></b> to save your changes.</li>
     <br>
     <br> 
     <i><a href="http://www.screencast.com/t/soBnxtevt">Click here to view a video of the above process.</a></i> 
    </ul> 
    <h3><u>Installing or updating the GRCC Remote Access web client:</u></h3> 
    <ul> 
     <li>Browse to <b><i>https://remote.greenriver.edu.</i></b></li> 
     <li>Log in using your <b><i>employee credentials.</i></b></li> 
     <li>If the client is not installed, or is outdated, you will be prompted to download the current version. Click the <b><i>Download</i></b> button and select <b><i>Run</i></b>.<br><b><i>Please note the following:</i></b><br></li> 
     <li class="indent">You may be prompted with <b>two</b> security warnings. Select <b>Run</b> at each prompt.</li> 
     <li class="indent">Depending upon the speed of your internet connection and computer, there may be a delay before an "Installation Progress" screen appears. Please be patient as this could take up to a minute. When the installation is finished you will receive a confirmation dialogue. Click <b>Close</b> to continue.</li> 
     <li>Select the icon labeled <b><i>GRCC Remote Desktop</i></b> to complete the process and connect to the remote access server desktop.</li>
     <br>
     <br> 
     <i><a href="http://www.screencast.com/t/2qXilnjil">Click here to view a video of the above process.</a></i> 
    </ul> 
    <h3><u>Clearing internet cache and cookies:</u></h3> 
    <p class="cont">In some cases it may be necessary to delete your browser's internet cache and cookies. Use the procedures below to delete the cache and cookies in for your browser version.</p> 
    <h3><u>Internet Explorer</u></h3> 
    <ul> 
     <li>Open the Internet Explorer web browser.</li> 
     <li>Select <b><i>Tools</i></b>, and then select <b><i>Internet Options</i></b>.</li> 
     <li>Select the tab labeled <b><i>General</i></b>.</li> 
     <li>Under Browsing history, select <b><i>Delete</i></b></li> 
     <li>Under Temporary Internet Files, select <b><i>Delete files...</i></b></li> 
     <li>A confirmation dialogue will appear, select <b><i>Yes.</i></b></li> 
     <li>Under Cookies, select <b><i>Delete cookies...</i></b></li> 
     <li>A confirmation dialogue will appear, select <b><i>Yes.</i></b></li> 
     <li>Select <b><i>Close</i></b>, then select <b><i>OK.</i></b></li> 
    </ul> 
    <h3><u>Firefox:</u></h3> 
    <ul> 
     <li>Open the Firefox web browser.</li> 
     <li>Select <b><i>Tools</i></b>, and then select <b><i>Options</i></b>.</li> 
     <li>Select the icon labeled <b><i>Advanced</i></b> from the top section of the options panel.</li> 
     <li>Select the tab labeled <b><i>Network</i></b> and select <b><i>Clear Now.</i></b></li> 
     <li>Next select the icon labeled <b><i>Privacy</i></b> from the top section of the options panel.</li> 
     <li>Locate the section labeled <b><i>Private Data</i></b> and select <b><i>Clear Now.</i></b></li> 
     <li>Depending on your Firefox version, a screen labeled "Clear Private Data" may appear. If this screen appears, check the following items:</li> 
     <li class="indent">Browsing History</li> 
     <li class="indent">Download History</li> 
     <li class="indent">Cache</li> 
     <li class="indent">Cookies</li> 
     <li class="indent">Offline Website Data</li> 
     <li class="indent">Authenticated Sessions</li> 
     <li><b>Optionally</b> check the following items:</li> 
     <li class="indent">Saved Form and Search History</li> 
     <li class="indent">Saved Passwords (be certain you remember your saved passwords)</li> 
     <li>Select <b><i>Clear Private Data Now</i></b></li> 
     <li>Select <b><i>OK.</i></b></li>
     <br>
     <br> 
     <i><a href="http://www.google.com/support/accounts/bin/answer.py?hl=en&amp;answer=32050">Click here to view videos that demonstrate how to clear the internet cache in IE and Firefox.</a></i> 
    </ul> 
